    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Fulfill paid orders with Shopify and Google Sheets for your team\n\n**Pattern:** Order Fulfillment · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nFulfill paid orders with Shopify and Google Sheets for your team. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual order ops is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Pull Side A (Google Sheets) → Diff the Two Systems → Create Missing in Airtable → Gather Sync Results → Save Execution Metadata → Tag Pipeline Metadata → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to order fulfillment without manual effort\n- Anyone automating order ops in e-commerce\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Responds in seconds\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Airtable PAT; Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2; Twilio SID + token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "3ea71d41-dcba-78d9-eaa3-bee7c4c2e534",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -620
      ],
      "id": "cedcaa92-b663-fdc8-66e3-5b9a2ad496ba",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -620
      ],
      "id": "29cd4d29-5379-43fd-57dc-63bdeb9fc92b",
      "name": "🔐 Security"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        610,
        -620
      ],
      "id": "8c292764-79c4-fcf1-e629-57fe219b8840",
      "name": "🧹 Data quality"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your order ops process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
